metadata.name: Trajectories #36
metadata.description: No one knows how life will turn out.¬† Sometimes you cross another person's path.  Sometimes you don't.¬† Sometimes your paths diverge.¬† Sometimes you double back on yourself, or meet a dead-end.¬† Sometimes you stay in your lane.¬† Sometimes you break free, whilst others are held back.¬† Sometimes you are held back.¬† Sometimes you find your self going against the flow, sometimes with it.¬† Sometimes the path is complex, when there are so many possibilities.¬† Sometimes the path is clear and simple.

metadata.name: Shape of 2 #44
metadata.description:
My second minimalist generative token is about a ‚ÄôShape of 2‚Äô. 
2 vertical sets of fine lines create ONE sculpture. The left versus the right side can be either mirrored, show similar or even oppositional expressions - depending on the generated length of the horizontal lines. A ‚ÄôShape of 2‚Äô might remind one of a classic vase, a river or a sculpture - depending on its body language.

metadata.name: Action; System #8
metadata.description:
Action; system is an experimental study inspired by the work of Fran√ßois Morellet. Morellet was one of the founders of the Groupe de Recherche d'Art Visuel (GRAV), founded in the 60s. His work was often informed by systems, a set of rules that determine the artwork, reducing the artist's subjectivity to a minimum.

This work explores what happens when we let go of the strict rule set. Do we ever fully let go?

-----------------
This work was released for the 2023 fundraising exhibition Cure3, and all of the proceeds and 1% of royalties will go to Parkinson's research funds. You can find more information at https://cure3.co.uk/.

-----------------
Controls
- R: new randomized output (the chances of recovering one of these outputs are very slim, that's what the next control is for)
- E: high-res output
- Double click: fullscreen

While you see the eye of Horus, your artwork is loading.

------------------
Made with p5.js & glsl
License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

metadata.name: Shining Clusters #29
metadata.description:
In each piece, the amazing space of the nebula is simulated at random.
This project explores a small part of the movement of nebulae, combining real-world imagery and imagination to show how nebulae move.
- A nebula is a bright and distinct cloud of interstellar gas that forms as a result of ionization, neutral hydrogen cells, and cosmic dust.
The interior of nebulas can be compared to an painting that is created naturally in space.

Made by p5.js

metadata.name: glory hole$ #329
metadata.description:
our consciousness as humans can be distilled into a crudely fashioned hole at an abandoned dave & busters and the meditative state that is endured while sitting on a neglected toilet praying for the sound of disrupted waters. glory holes embody anonymity and pleasure for pleasure's sake. they are creations that cannot be destroyed, as they exist in the memories of anyone who uses or witnesses. many speculate that the carving of the hole is the purest form of human ingenuity and the desire to explore the unknown. formerly limited to the physical space. these glory holes transcend space and time. and exist in that same unknown that tempts us all. legalize ground beef. create nothing. consume everything.

HUGE thank you to @PureSpider for the layered PNG template, this dream would not have been realized without you friend.

metadata.name: Paper Mandala #16
metadata.description:
A collaboration with P1xelboy and Paper Buddha.
Beautiful paper mandalas made purely with code in Paper Buddha's style.
Features include:
27 different palettes
3 different mandala types (Lotus, Starburst Style 1 and Starburst Style 2)
Four sections of the mandala with one of 10 different pattern types (Dots, Checks, Crosses, Triangles, Stripes, Circles, Polygons, Lazers, Quadrants and Hatching)
4 different direction types of shadow - of varying length
Randomly placed star background
Randomly placed Nebula
Possible Special Pattern Effect with darker stippling pattern
Possible Nirvana Effect where random colors are added to one of either Golden, Silver, Bronze, Blue Moon or Sea Green palettes.

Using only code, this produces a unique output which does take a few seconds to load.
Press "S" to Save your unique Paper Mandala as a 2048 x 2048 JPG
Press "R" for a random shuffle effect - (please wait for reload) - Refresh page to reset

The project works in a responsive browser, so to set up for phone background or watch, resize the browser accordingly and Alt + Print Screen to get an appropriately sized image.

Offered as a Dutch Auction, holders of the first 20 tokens (1-20) will receive additional benefits in the form of utility for future releases in the P1xelboy/Paper Mandala collaboration series. (exact details to be determined)
This utility will remain attached to tokens 1-20 and transfer to the new owner upon subsequent secondary sales.

Uses p5.js and p5.pattern
@p1x3lboy @paperbuddha - September 2022

metadata.name: Mountains Waves and Valleys #25
metadata.description:
This work is an animated series of lines with various elements of chaos and phase shifting. Emergent graphics can resemble waves, mountains, or graphics. It can feel energized, meditative, chaotic, or harmonious. 

Configurable Parameters:
- Animation Speed
- Chaos Amplifier: Adds extra amplitude and randomness to the waves
- Color Palette: 20 different settings
- Curved Lines: Toggle between smooth curves and angular lines
- Line Complexity: Number of points in each line
- Line Weight: 6 options
- Line Space: 3 options for vertical spacing
- Layout Mode: 5 options
- Peak Height: 4 options
- Valleys: Toggle visibility of valleys
- Wave Offset: Similarity or difference of waves
